		<div id ="title">
			<h1 >APJ Abdul Kalam</h1>
			<p>The missile man of India</p>
		</div>
		
		<figure id="img-div"> 
			<img id = "image" src="https://i.ndtvimg.com/i/2016-12/apj-abdul-kalam_650x400_51481193286.jpg" alt="Image of Apj Abdul Kalam">
			<figcaption id="img-caption" > The President, Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam addressing the nation on the eve of 58th Republic Day, in New Delhi on January 25, 2007.
			 </figcaption>		
		</figure>

		<article id="tribute-info">
				<p> <strong>Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam</strong>,born on October 15, 1931 in Rameshwaram Tamil Nadu. Studied physics and aerospace engineering. 
				Devoted 4 decades of his lifetime as a sciemtist and a science administrator for the Drdo and the isro. 
			 He was deeply involved in the Indian civilian space programme and  militray missile development efforts. </p>
			<section id="key-evnets">			
			<h3>Notable Years:</h3> 
			 <ul>
				<li><b>1960</b> Graduated from Madras Institue of Technonlogy</li>	
				<li><b>1962</b> Posted at Thumba Equatorial Rocket Launching Station	</li>		 
				<li><b>1963</b> Joined ISRO (Indian Space Research Oraganisation)</li>
				<li><b>1964</b> Joined DRDO(Department of Research and Development Organisation) as a technical assistant</li>
				<li><b>1965</b> Started work on expandable rocket project independently at the DRDO	</li>
				<li><b>1968</b> Formed the Indian rocket Society</li>
				<li><b>1969</b> Transfered to the ISRO where he was the project director of the SLV-III (Satellite Lauch Vehicle) launched the Rohini satteleit to the near earth orbit in 1980</li>
				<li><b>1970</b> Directed  Project Devil and Project valient which sought to develop ballistic missile from the technology of the SLV programme</li>				
				<li><b>1973</b> Appointed Project Director of SLV-3</li>
				<li><b>1979</b> Successful launch of SLV-III launch on August 10 with Kalam as Mission Director</li>
				<li><b>1980</b> Second mission of SLV-III successful too</li>
				<li><b>1981</b> Awarded Padma Bhushan</li>
				<li><b>1982</b> Rejoined DRDO, conceived the Integrated Guided Missile Development Programme (IGMDP) for indigenous missiles</li>
				<li><b>1982</b> Appointed Director DRDL</li>
				<li><b>1983</b> Missile programme launched</li>
				<li><b>1985</b> Trishul test-fired</li>
				<li><b>1989</b> Agni test-fired</li>
				<li><b>1992</b> Appointed Scientific Adviser to Defense Minister and Secretary, Department of Defense Research & Development</li>
				<li><b>1997</b> Awarded Bharat Ratna</li>
				<li><b>1998</b> Underground nuclear tests near Pokharan on May 11</li>
				<li><b>1998</b> Appointed Principal Scientific Advisor to the Government of India</li>
				<li><b>1998</b> Writes India 2020: A Vision for the New Millennium with YS Rajan</li>
				<li><b>1998</b> Developed a low cost coronary stent along with the cardiologist Soma Raju, a device used for maintaining the coronary blood flow after the angioplasty</li>
				<li><b>1999</b> AGNI-II missile system successfully tested in April</li>
				<li><b>1999</b> Polar Satellite Launch Vehicle launched on 26 May</li>
				<li><b>2001</b> Retires as Principal Scientific Advisor to the Government of India</li>
				<li><b>2002</b> Succeeded K. R. Narayan as the 11th president of india.</li>
			 </ul>
			 
			 </section>
